se your MDS with a shield?  Would it need +300hp and +20 to all saves?  AC 150 and 25 sta?  <br><br>I understand the saying that Marlowe (I think) coined, ie &quot;Offense stacks, Defense does not,&quot; and its implications regarding the value of a shield.  With that very fact in mind, what would a shield have to do to make you use it over a two hander? <p>Aragir Lancot<BR>"One man plus the truth equals a majority."<BR>Cerivel tells you, 'Hehe grats on scaring off a level 56 giant that hits for 360'<BR><BR>Paladin of the 49th shield<BR><a href="http://www.emeraldis.com/~booraembj/">Exiles</a>, Xegony<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/udrachan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Drachan</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/misc_2.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 113<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/14/02 6:19:47 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=203.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What would make you want to use a shield?</span><hr size=1> Well most obivous interest of shield is AC, so shields with higher ACs would be nice. And I don't mean that these shold be the super rare, 2 per server drops only available from nToV.<br><br>There should be shields as common as SBS with an AC of 40 or 50 to them.<br><br>But more than the shields themselves, it could be new AA skills thied to shields that might be a savior.<br><br>AA points just give verant the perfect tool.<br><br>Skills that would give or increase chances to stun, to knock back, to avoid AoE dmg (i e take cover behing shield to avoid breathweapon, rain, etc.), or simply a skill that would increase the AC benefit of a shield in incremental steps of 15% up to a max of 45 or 60% maybe, dunno, would need testing. The latter would make many existing shields stay useful. (SBS would in effect yield AC 40 instead of 25, Fearsome shield would be 64 instead of 40<br>A bit of imagination and tuning to make it balanced.<br><br>Let's not forget the 2HS incease was made essentially to compensate us non dual wielding tanks (PAL and SHD) vs all other melee classes who can all dual wield, so the focus shold not be on dmg, but on AC or other abilities for shield improvement.<br><br>And down to the core a shield is created to protect form blows, so AC increase would be my favorite, or alternatively a special dmg reduction effect, as there exsits a similar AA skill, which would stack with the latter.<br>Or an AA skill that would increase parry and dodge by a certain amount when using a shield (stackable with other similar AA skills that do the same).<br>Increasing bash skill to 250 would be a small start <p><div align="center"><font size="2"><i><font face="Times New Roman, Times, serif"><b><font color="#CCCCCC">Drachan de Rocfaucon, the Silversword </font></b></font></i></font><br><b><font size="1">Knight of the Prime Healer</font> </b><br><b><i><font size="1">Member of the  <font face="blacc_.ttf" color="#FFCC00">Crusaders of Faith</font></font></i><font size="1"><br></font> </b> </div></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/udrachan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Drachan</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/misc_2.gif" BORDER=0> at: 3/14/02 6:21:17 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ueggolas.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Eggolas</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 25<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/14/02 6:28:22 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=203.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What would make you want to use a shield?</span><hr size=1> Paladins are the masters of spell interrupts (potentially) amongst the melee classes, so I'd prefer AA points being used to increase likelihood of a spell interrupt from a bash and possibly a faster reset time (AA = more arm strength and faster recovery).<br><br>I would also like to see AA points tied to another shield characteristic - deflection (highly polished shield?).  Spell has chance to be resisted and deflected onto an enemy mob, perhaps 5% at AA1, 10% at AA2 and 15% or 20% at AA3.<br><br>Fun to play around with the idea. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukidkod1ak.showPublicProfile?language=EN>kidkod1ak</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 156<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/14/02 7:03:22 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=203.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What would make you want to use a shield?</span><hr size=1> I think the use of a shield should be highly valuable before your even able to make AA exp. I think the clearest cut method of providing that is a block skill, similar to dodge and parry but requires a shield to be equipped. This is afterall the reason shield were invented, to block blows. <p><bold><a href = "http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=101014">Varner Rapscallion</a> <br>58 Knight of Brell<br> Master Brewer, Fletcher, Potter, Baker</bold></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/udrachan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Drachan</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/misc_2.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 114<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/14/02 7:50:16 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=203.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What would make you want to use a shield?</span><hr size=1> The idea is nice Varner, in essence that would be the same effect as parry or dodge, i. e. avoid a blow.<br><br>So rather than have to work up yet another skill remove the parry cap with shield for paladins. I could envision parry skill with shield (what you call block) up to 255, like the defense skill.<br><br>And add an AA to increase this block skill probability with shield.<br><br>That would work in the sense of the paladin's defensive paradigm and work in the sense of giving back value to shields.<br> <p><div align="center"><font size="2"><i><font face="Times New Roman, Times, serif"><b><font color="#CCCCCC">Drachan de Rocfaucon, the Silversword </font></b></font></i></font><br><b><font size="1">Knight of the Prime Healer</font> </b><br><b><i><font size="1">Member of the  <font face="blacc_.ttf" color="#FFCC00">Crusaders of Faith</font></font></i><font size="1"><br></font> </b> </div></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uangelsyn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Angelsyn</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://members.aol.com/tdlutenatenjou/icon_keyne.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 163<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/14/02 7:54:33 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=203.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/tdlutenatenjou/icon_keyne.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What would make you want to use a shield?</span><hr size=1> Varner has my idea exactly...<br><br>The Block Skill, tied to the use of a Shield, would make a Shield very valuable.<br><br>Cap the skill at 75-100, then put Shields in the game with +10% or +20% to Block... and maybe procs on shields as well.<br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Great Shield of the Ykesha</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>Secondary<br>AC 30<br>+5 Str, +5 Wis, +5 Int, +50 Mana, +10% MR<br>+10% Block<br>Effect: Ykesha (Combat)<br>Wt: 6.0<br><br>That would be a very nice upper-40's/lower-50's shield. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utiriantrueblade.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tirian Trueblade</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://home.earthlink.net/~asercion/iconsg.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 430<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/14/02 8:15:23 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=203.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.earthlink.net/~asercion/tirianicon.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What would make you want to use a shield?</span><hr size=1> Just curious about the proc idea, would it have a chance to proc only when you Bash?  I usually save my Bash for a spell cast, so I don't use it very much, meaning I wouldn't proc often at all if that was the case.  Obviously this is only discussion, but I wonder if Verant would be able to implement a proc on a shield not tied to Bash?<br><br>I'm all for getting some nice effects or significantly increased stats on shields though.  Right now using a shield is more of an afterthought for many of us, only when we have obtained a nice 1H weapon like the DMF or Massive Dragonclaw Shard.  I'd like the shields themselves to be the reason we consider using them, not just because we have that secondary slot free. <p><img src= "http://home.earthlink.net/~asercion/tirsigns.jpg"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usenchy.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Senchy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 286<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/14/02 8:39:31 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=203.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What would make you want to use a shield?</span><hr size=1> An interesting concept might be the ability to hide behind a shield during a dragons breath, reducing the damage significantly. That would make shields a very viable option for dragon/tov raids. <br><br>It could similar act on meele damage. While using the &quot;guard&quot; skill meele damage taken from a mob would be reduced but all casting/meele from a player would be paused during that also.<br><br>So when a shield wearing player gets unwanted aggro, they could raise the shield and guard themselves. Possible give an NPC a chance to knock the shield out of guard position for increase damage taken.<br><br><br><br><br><br> <p>Senchy Solariatus60 Crusader of Rodcet Nife55 Chanter of Rodcet Nife (Tymbor)Dol Amroth<BR><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=79641>My Profile</a><BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ugilfalas.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gilfalas</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Administrator</span><br>  Posts: 1423<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/14/02 11:42:57 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=203.topic&index=8>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What would make you want to use a shield?</span><hr size=1> Adding the Block skill while a shield is equipped is an idea in the right direction.<br><br>Leaving it capped at 75-100 I think would be WAY too low. Capping it at say 175-180 is more realistic. After all if your going to lose about 25% of your melee damage or more, you may as well receive a 15-20% defense increase for the choice.<br><br>So far shields give maybe 1-3% defense increase with just AC adds. <p><center><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=105286">Gilfalas Elaandrin</a>, Lvl 59 Knight of Tunare & Defender of Nature<br>Bertoxxulous Server<br><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/bpaladinsofnorrath">Paladins Of Norrath</a> Messageboard Admin<br>Member of <a href="http://www.fedupnow.com/">Dragon Council</a><br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uwhitchywhon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Whitchywhon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 131<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/14/02 12:51:12 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=203.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What would make you want to use a shield?</span><hr size=1> I use my shield for interrupting casters.<br>Raising BASH skill is SLOW.<br>I neglected 1hs for 2 lvls and i got it up using a yak and a haste buff from groupmate.<br>But bash is still behind  :-(<br><br>Could they do something like in Diablo2<br>Where some shields add to the %chance 