frm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=203.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What would make you want to use a shield?</span><hr size=1> Milords, Being only a veteran of 40 seasons, I know not the import of AC in a highend raid. However, like I, there are Paladins out there that believe that the true weapons of a Holy Knight are the Sword and Shield, not the 2hs or 2hb many favor for high damage output.<br><br>I play in this world because it gives me joy to swing a sword and shield in a just cause. For those of us who are like minded, it would be nice to see VI create some shield skills strictly for Paladins (and our evil couterparts, the Shadowknights) similiar to what is found in Diablo II. But that will not change the way I play. <br><br>Just my 2cp. <p>Nathanielsan StarbladePaladin, 40th Season(A)bort, (R)etry, (I)nfluence with Sword and Shield!</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uabazagaroth.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Abazagaroth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 134<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/14/02 2:41:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=203.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.humanevolution.f2s.com/images/webring.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What would make you want to use a shield?</span><hr size=1> Nathanielsan: You'll go 2h, we all do, its simply stupid otherwise.<br><br>We can come up with all this complicated stuff, but it isn't going to happen and would take forever for them to code and implement. I think the best answer is pretty damn simple:<br><br>Put paladin and sks' 1h damage on the 2h damage table.<br><br>Think about it, what are the best 2h weapons? Things with ratios not much different than the best 1hers. I can think of very few 1hers that would be overpowered versus the 2hers that drop from the same or comparable mobs in comparable places. Is Dawncaller much better than Great Spear of Dawn if both are on 2h damage table? It looks like it would be a bit better (Luthair's calculator puts it at like 10 percent more damage or so, but it underestimates higher damage weapons, and so its probably close to the same). You should sacrifice a bit of damage for the stats/ac gain of using a shield, but the slight nerf needed to &quot;balance&quot; the 1h for paladins and sks wouldn't be too severe, and would still have them doing far more damage than they do now.<br><br>Hell, to use a 1h you have to also get a shield, which in an item based game like this should be considered in the cost. IMHO 1h weapons with comparable difficulty in obtaining should do 5-10% less damage than the comparable two hander. I mean, the stats/ac from the shield aren't even going to make up from that.<br><br>So I say, leave shields as is, move the 1h damage of paladins and sks to our 2h damage table, and nerf 1h weapons that need it appropriately (to be honest, except for maybe the massive dragonclaw shard and DMF, I can't see any of the 1hers that would really need to be nerfed to keep the risk vs. reward in line, and then only slightly). <br><br>Baron Abazagaroth Katzkortulu<br>Knight of The Rathe<br><br>P.S. If they made 1hers worth it, I would use a 1h over a 2h in a heartbeat, as I'm sure many many paladins would, because most of us are sword and shield guys. And make some NPC to turn in FA/FDs for a 1h fiery weapon damnit!<br> <p>C. David Kreger, dkreger@yahoo.com<br>Webmaster:<br><a href="http://www.humanevolution.f2s.com" target="_top">A Look at Modern Human Origins</a><br>Moderator:<br><a href="http://pub19.ezboard.com/balookatmodernhumanorigins" target="_top">Human Evolution Message Board</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666