<td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What would make you want to use a shield?</span><hr size=1> To the person that likes 1HS and Shield for RP reasons:  I used to be the same way.  I used Ghoulbane basically until I was able to afford Sword of The Morning, and used that until 52.  It was around then I realized that I wasn't contributing much at all to the fight in groups, espeically small groups.  I could easily outtaunt others and keep my group safe, but the healers were wasting a lot of mana on me because the mobs simply wouldn't die fast enough.  I remember slow duoing sessions with my RL Druid friend using his DoTs and Damage Shields to supplement my melee damage.  They were SLOW.  When I changed over to a nice 2H weapon, (30/35) they went so much faster.  <br><br>I'm all for trying to fit the image you have in your mind, but for me personally, my image was costing my friends experience and wasting much of their time.  I decided that wasn't a sacrifice I was going to force on them any longer when my own vanity was the cause.<br><br>Once I can get a nice one hand weapon, I'll gladly switch to it and look for a really nice shield to compliment it, but as it stands, no shield is worth going to a sub-par 1H like SoTM unless you need the resists for a Dragon type raid.  Even then, you aren't helping the raid much with the little damage you contribute unless you are main tanking it.<br><br>Just my opinion anyway. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><img src= "http://home.earthlink.net/~asercion/tirsigns.jpg"></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page  <b>1</b> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showMessageRange?topicID=203.topic&start=21&stop=24>2</a> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showPrevM